# ✅ 2. Permanently Mount EBS (Very Important for Lab)

This ensures data stays after reboot.

---

## 🔹 Step 1: Check Disk

```bash
lsblk
```

Example new disk:

```
/dev/nvme1n1
```

---

## 🔹 Step 2: Create Partition

```bash
sudo fdisk /dev/nvme1n1
```

Inside fdisk:

```
n
p
Enter
Enter
Enter
w
```

Then:

```bash
sudo partprobe
```

---

## 🔹 Step 3: Format Disk

```bash
sudo mkfs.xfs /dev/nvme1n1p1
```

---

## 🔹 Step 4: Create Folder

```bash
sudo mkdir /mnt/data
```

---

## 🔹 Step 5: Mount Volume

```bash
sudo mount /dev/nvme1n1p1 /mnt/data
```

Verify:

```bash
df -h
```

---

## 🔹 Step 6: Make Permanent (VERY IMPORTANT)

Get UUID:

```bash
sudo blkid
```

Copy UUID of nvme1n1p1

Edit:

```bash
sudo nano /etc/fstab
```

Add line:

```
UUID=your-uuid-here   /mnt/data   xfs   defaults,nofail   0   0
```

Save & exit.

Test:

```bash
sudo mount -a
```

---

## 🔹 Step 7: Test Persistence

```bash
sudo reboot
```

After reconnect:

```bash
df -h
```

🎉 Volume automatically mounted.

